data.description: Live your Florida dream in this 2019 coastal-style on an elevated slab. As you walk in, you're welcomed by an open floor plan that feels spacious and inviting, featuring wood-like tile floors, neutral walls, and elegant granite countertops—making it the perfect place for gatherings. The modern kitchen is a joy for anyone who loves to cook, with tall cabinets that have crown molding, shiny stainless steel appliances, designer lighting, and a window up high that fills the room with natural light. The split floor plan provides a private retreat in the master bedroom, which comes with an en-suite bathroom featuring two walk-in closets, a beautifully tiled shower enclosed in glass, and plenty of natural light enhanced by stylish light fixtures. The additional bedrooms are positioned at the back of the house, sharing a well-designed bathroom that's ideal for guests. For those in need of extra space, the oversized garage boasts 16-foot ceilings and offers room for storage and multiple vehicles. Additional features include an indoor laundry room with a washer and dryer, an elevated outdoor HVAC system, and plenty of storage space throughout the house. Step outside, and you'll discover not just one, but two outdoor areas for relaxation—a covered patio in the back perfect for winding down after a day on the water and a front porch that's just right for enjoying the sunset. Large windows and a glass-etched front door allow for ample natural light, making the home feel bright and welcoming. Don't wait for a new build; this dream home is move-in ready and waiting for you. Conveniently located just a short distance from Little Harbor and Shell Point Marina, you're never far from the beach and aquatic adventures. Schedule your private tour today and begin living your coastal dream!
